Marcelino Perea VELASQUEZ v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6686. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. June 9, 1961. No attorney for appellant. John Quinn, U. S. Atty., Albuquerque, N. M., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BRATTON and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed June 9, 1961, without written opinion, on authority of Martin v. United States of America, 10 Cir., 285 F.2d 150.
